# DIG Browser: the CONTROL PANE toolbar button + the dig://control full page.
#
# A dedicated toolbar button (the DIG control mark, dig_control.icon) sits next
# to the wallet + shields buttons. UNLIKE the wallet/shields buttons (which DOCK
# in Chromium's Side Panel), the Control Pane button NAVIGATES THE ACTIVE TAB to
# a FULL PAGE at dig://control — a normal top-level navigation (WindowOpenDisposition::
# CURRENT_TAB), the way dig://home/about/welcome are full pages. It is the
# browser-as-CONTROLLER surface: it manages the user's local dig-node.
#
# dig://control IS the node-controller surface. To stay DRY and never let two
# copies of the (large) controller page drift, the dig loader serves the SAME
# embedded controller page (kDigNodeHtml, with the loopback control token
# injected) for BOTH the dig://node host (the legacy, omnibox-only entry) and the
# new dig://control host — so the Control Pane is exactly the proven My Node
# controller, reachable from a first-class toolbar button. The page itself does
# the honest branch: if a LOCAL dig-node answers at dig.local/localhost it shows
# the management UI driven by the control.* admin RPCs; if none answers it shows
# the install landing nudging the user to download a dig-node. Browsing is never
# gated on a node — chia:// reads transparently fall back to rpc.dig.net; only the
# management UI requires a local node. (The pure page-posture policy + a no-drift
# guard live in dig/control/dig_control.mjs + dig_control.test.mjs.)
#
# The button class (DigControlButton) mirrors DigShieldsButton (windows-dig-
# shields.patch) but is stripped of all side-panel/SidePanelUI code: its press
# handler does a single CURRENT_TAB Navigate(GURL("dig://control")). It is
# registered into the toolbar right after the shields button. The dig_control.icon
# is registered in chrome/app/vector_icons/BUILD.gn (beside dig_shield/dig_wallet,
# added by windows-dig-browser-ux.patch) and the dig://control host dispatch is a
# one-line extension of the existing dig://node branch in dig_url_loader_factory.cc
# (windows-dig-browser-ux.patch). Applies AFTER windows-dig-sidepanel.patch.
